# Path to the data
file_path = 'Real-Time_Traffic_Incident_Reports.csv'

# Load the data into a DataFrame 
df = pd.read_csv(file_path)

df['Published Date'] = pd.to_datetime(df['Published Date'])

start_date = '01-01-2019'
end_date = '12-31-2019'

mask = (df['Published Date'] > start_date) & (df['Published Date'] < end_date)

df = df.loc[mask]

mask2 = (df['Issue Reported'] == 'Crash Urgent')

df = df.loc[mask2]

mask3 = (df['Latitude'] > 30.1) & (df['Latitude'] < 30.5)

df = df.loc[mask3]

mask4 = (df['Longitude'] > -97.9) & (df['Longitude'] < 97.6)

df = df.loc[mask4]

In [8]:
#clusters
x = df.iloc[:,4:6]
x

wcss=[]
for i in range(1,20):
    kmeans = KMeans(i)
    kmeans.fit(x)
    wcss_iter = kmeans.inertia_
    wcss.append(wcss_iter)

number_clusters = range(1,20)
plt.plot(number_clusters,wcss)
plt.title('The Elbow title')
plt.xlabel('Number of clusters')
plt.ylabel('WCSS')
